ols at the end of the course were skipped\nnc: not competing\nthe competitor is not eligible for standings, such as when running a second course\ndq: disqualified\nbreaking competition rules, such as conferring with another competitor or entering an out of bounds area\novt: overtime\nreturning after the course closure time\ndns: did not start\nthe competitor did not start\n<time>*\nthe star indicates course completion status was not reported and may be valid, msp, or dnf","external_links":[{"link_url":"http://obasen.orientering.se/winsplits/online/en/default.asp?page=classes&databaseId=66075","link_type":"splits"},{"link_url":"http://rg.cascadeoc.org/rg2/#266","link_type":"splits"}],"volunteer_roles":[{"role_name":"Control Pickup","individual_id":"019d0a11-4d2f-7bd2-9195-69486afb3aad","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Dan Thrush","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Control Pickup","individual_id":"019b7acf-182c-7c41-bf38-2f166390b465","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Eric Bone","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Control Pickup","individual_id":"019d0a11-4d30-7bb4-9ef1-5b9711d308a6","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Olivier Baxa","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Control Pickup","individual_id":"019b810b-3de3-7b31-a4c6-3221eaa84e1a","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Rob Knudsen","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Control Pickup","individual_id":"019b7b13-3219-7a2c-93f7-0d0d45e15e8e","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Sue Kuestner","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Course Designer","individual_id":"019d0a11-4d30-710f-b42f-ecba537a7836","citation_count":2,"individual_name":"Ott Toomet","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Course Designer","individual_id":"019d0a11-4d30-76ee-9a0d-1d875a72b54f","citation_count":2,"individual_name":"Peteris Ledins","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Epunch Coordinator","individual_id":"01913919-da03-757e-b829-aa2bdc684400","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Debbie Newell","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Finish","individual_id":"01913919-da03-757e-b829-aa2bdc684400","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Debbie Newell","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Finish","individual_id":"019d0a11-4d2f-78a9-8722-6f8ceafbfa42","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Gina Nuss","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Meet Director","individual_id":"019d0a11-4d2f-736d-863f-5e546e61e969","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Ing Uhlin","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Registration","individual_id":"019d0a11-4d2f-7ca3-bac0-7b273197ba3f","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Bethany Rentz","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Start","individual_id":"019d0a11-4d30-73a6-9f55-9583d8329fee","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Jenny Conley","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null}],"organizing_club_id":"01912f3e-e3e1-7e8e-b3c6-32387a8b4990","result_source_brief":"CascadeOC Website: https://www.cascadeoc.org/result/baltic-cup-teanaway-day-2-jungle-creek/","organizing_club_name":"Cascade Orienteering Club","cumulative_event_comments":"Baltic Cup at Teanaway Day 1 – Jack Creek\n\nMaximum time on course is 2 hours. You have to return to the finish after 2 hours from your start punch, even if you haven’t completed the course, and even if the course is not closed yet.\nMaximum time on course is 3 hours. You have to return to the finish after 2 hours from your start punch, even if you haven’t completed the course, and even if the course is not closed yet.\nThis is a double header weekend Sept 28-29 on Peteris Ledins’s maps around the Twenty-nine Pines Campground on Teanaway Rd N Fork.\nSaturday: Middle distance, courses north of Jack Creek (east of Teanaway Rd N Fork)\nSunday: Long distance, courses south of Jungle Creek (west of 29 Pines Campground).\nOn Saturday, Registration will be at the 29 Pines Campground. On Sunday, Registration will be by the Finish for Day 2. (See staging map)\nBeginner instruction with mini-course on Saturday 11:00 am, by Registration at 29 Pines Campground.\nThere will be an assigned start list for the M21+ and F21+ classes on Day 1. This is in preparation for our club’s participation as start organizers in NAOC 2020.\nSafety: All participants must carry a whistle on the courses.\nTeanaway Cup takes place around Teanaway North Fork river, near the 29 Pines campground (free but Discover pass needed). All starts and finishes are from walking distance (but rather long) from the campground. Finish is relatively closer to the campground.\nThe venue is mostly forested where the vegetation ranges between open pine forests to dense thickets of vine maple and salal. The area is hilly and a long walk to start is needed to avoid too much climb on the course. The forest has burned two years ago and made the terrain in most cases more accessible. The forest has thorny underbrush in places; we recommend long pants and shin guards.\nAll courses have remote start: follow flagged route from the map issue point (start punch) to the start triangle (just flag, no punch there). Note: you have to follow the marked route to the start triangle flag, free route choice begins thereafter.\nFor successful navigation on all courses, except White, you should understand landforms and how these are represented on the map with contours. In particular, you should know what are re-entrants and spurs, how these are represented on the map and on the control description.\n\nThank you to all volunteers for helping make this event a success!\nYellow Course (3.0k, 10 controls, 35m climb): no participants\nResult Status Codes\nmsp: missing punch\na control was skipped or taken out of order\ndnf: did not finish\na control or set of controls at the end of the course were skipped\nnc: not competing\nthe competitor is not eligible for standings, such as when running a second course\ndq: disqualified\nbreaking competition rules, such as conferring with another competitor or entering an out of bounds area\novt: overtime\nreturning after the course closure time\ndns: did not start\nthe competitor did not start\n<time>*\nthe star indicates course completion status was not reported and may be valid, msp, or dnf"}
